file.name: openapi.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.2
info:
  description: |-
    Through the Universal Screening API, you can access the power of FactSet's Universal Screening Application.
    Calculate and return the results of your saved Universal Screens.
  title: Universal Screening API
  version: 0.0.1
servers:
- url: /
security:
- FactSetApiKey: []
- FactSetOAuth2: []
paths:
  /v1/archive:
    post:
      description: Begins archive of screen to OFDB
      operationId: SubmitArchiveOFDB
      requestBody:
        $ref: '#/components/requestBodies/submitArchiveOFDBRequest'
      responses:
        "202":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Successful archive OFDB submission response, returns the job
            ID unique to this archive and the URL in the Location header to check
            the status of the archive.
          headers:
            Location:
              description: Relative location to poll for archive status
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
              description: Maximum number of jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
              description: Number of available jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "400":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid request body.
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "429":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Too many requests.
          headers:
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
              description: Maximum number of jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
              description: Number of available jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-contentType: application/json
      x-accepts: application/json
  /v1/archive/{id}/status:
    get:
      description: Polls the archive OFDB job with a given archive job ID and returns
        job status
      operationId: PollArchiveOFDB
      parameters:
      - description: Unique identifier for a screen archive to OFDB job
        explode: false
        in: path
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        style: simple
      responses:
        "201":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Archive job completed
          headers:
            X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
              description: Screen archive progress
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "202":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Archive job still in progress
          headers:
            Location:
              description: Relative location to poll for archive status
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
              description: Screen archive progress
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Job ID not found.
        "410":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: The results have been fetched for this ID.
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-accepts: application/json
  /v1/calculations:
    delete:
      description: Delete all active jobs started by the requester's username-serial
      operationId: DeleteAllActiveJobs
      responses:
        "204":
          description: No Content
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Job ID not found.
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-accepts: application/json
    get:
      description: Retrieve list of all active job ids started by requester's username-serial
      operationId: GetAllActiveJobs
      responses:
        "200":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200'
          description: ActiveJobsResponse contains id of all of a user's active jobs
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Job ID not found.
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-accepts: application/json
    post:
      description: Begins calculation of screen
      operationId: SubmitCalculate
      requestBody:
        $ref: '#/components/requestBodies/submitCalcRequest'
      responses:
        "202":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Successful calculation submission response, returns the job
            ID unique to this calculation and the URL in the Location header to check
            the status of the calculation.
          headers:
            Location:
              description: Relative location to poll for calculation status
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
              description: Maximum number of jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
              description: Number of available jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "400":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid request body.
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "429":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Too many requests.
          headers:
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
              description: Maximum number of jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
              description: Number of available jobs.
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-contentType: application/json
      x-accepts: application/json
  /v1/calculations/{id}:
    delete:
      description: Delete a specified job started by the requester's username-serial
      operationId: DeleteActiveJob
      parameters:
      - description: Unique identifier for a screen calculation job
        explode: false
        in: path
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        style: simple
      responses:
        "204":
          description: No content
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Job ID not found.
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-accepts: application/json
    get:
      description: Retrieve results of complete screen calculation. Screens with more
        than 10,000 rows will be returned in a paginated format. Results may be fetched
        in pages of 1,000 - 100,000 results with 10,000 being the default page size.
      operationId: GetCalculateResults
      parameters:
      - description: Unique identifier for a screen calculation job
        explode: false
        in: path
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        style: simple
      - description: Page size limit (minumum 1000, default 10,000, maximum 100,000)
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: _paginationLimit
        required: false
        schema:
          type: integer
        style: form
      - description: Paging index (Initial request may omit)
        explode: true
        in: query
        name: _paginationCursor
        required: false
        schema:
          type: integer
        style: form
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Screen calculation complete. The screen results will be formatted
            as a STACH 2.0 table and in a property named data. In the case of pagination
            column metadata will only be returned with the first page. Results will
            be purged after they are retrieved or six hours.
        "202":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Calculation job still in progress
          headers:
            Location:
              description: Relative location to poll for calculation status
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
              description: Screen calculation progress
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "400":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: The requested screen could not be opened.
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Job ID not found.
        "410":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: The results have been fetched for this ID.
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-accepts: application/json
  /v1/calculations/{id}/status:
    get:
      description: Polls the calculation job with a given screen calculation ID and
        returns job status
      operationId: PollCalculate
      parameters:
      - description: Unique identifier for a screen calculation job
        explode: false
        in: path
        name: id
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        style: simple
      responses:
        "201":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Calculation job completed
          headers:
            Location:
              description: Relative location to pick up screen calculation results
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
              description: Screen calculation progress
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "202":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
          description: Calculation job still in progress
          headers:
            Location:
              description: Relative location to poll for calculation status
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
            X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
              description: Screen calculation progress
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
        "401":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Invalid or missing authentication.
        "404":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: Job ID not found.
        "410":
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
          description: The results have been fetched for this ID.
        "500":
          description: Internal Server Error
          headers:
            Request-Key:
              description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
              explode: false
              schema:
                type: string
              style: simple
      tags:
      - ""
      x-accepts: application/json
components:
  parameters:
    ArchiveID:
      description: Unique identifier for a screen archive to OFDB job
      explode: false
      in: path
      name: id
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
      style: simple
    PaginationCursor:
      description: Paging index (Initial request may omit)
      explode: true
      in: query
      name: _paginationCursor
      required: false
      schema:
        type: integer
      style: form
    PaginationLimit:
      description: Page size limit (minumum 1000, default 10,000, maximum 100,000)
      explode: true
      in: query
      name: _paginationLimit
      required: false
      schema:
        type: integer
      style: form
    ScreenCalcID:
      description: Unique identifier for a screen calculation job
      explode: false
      in: path
      name: id
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
      style: simple
  requestBodies:
    submitArchiveOFDBRequest:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ScreenArchiveOFDBParameters'
      description: Data required for an archive to OFDB request
    submitCalcRequest:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ScreenCalcParameters'
      description: Data required for a calculation request
  responses:
    ActiveJobsResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200'
      description: ActiveJobsResponse contains id of all of a user's active jobs
    ArchiveOFDBInProgressResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
      description: Archive job still in progress
      headers:
        Location:
          description: Relative location to poll for archive status
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
          description: Screen archive progress
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    ArchiveOFDBSuccessResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
      description: Archive job completed
      headers:
        X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
          description: Screen archive progress
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    CalculateInProgressResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
      description: Calculation job still in progress
      headers:
        Location:
          description: Relative location to poll for calculation status
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
          description: Screen calculation progress
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    CalculateSuccessResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
      description: Calculation job completed
      headers:
        Location:
          description: Relative location to pick up screen calculation results
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-PickUp-Progress:
          description: Screen calculation progress
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    Error400InvalidRequest:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
      description: Invalid request body.
    Error400ScreenOpen:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
      description: The requested screen could not be opened.
    Error401Response:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
      description: Invalid or missing authentication.
    Error404Response:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
      description: Job ID not found.
    Error410Response:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
      description: The results have been fetched for this ID.
    Error429Response:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorArray'
      description: Too many requests.
      headers:
        X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
          description: Maximum number of jobs.
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
          description: Number of available jobs.
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    Generic500ErrorResponse:
      description: Internal Server Error
      headers:
        Request-Key:
          description: Provide this key when reporting this issue
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    SubmitArchiveOFDBResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
      description: Successful archive OFDB submission response, returns the job ID
        unique to this archive and the URL in the Location header to check the status
        of the archive.
      headers:
        Location:
          description: Relative location to poll for archive status
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
          description: Maximum number of jobs.
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
          description: Number of available jobs.
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
    SubmitCalculateResponse:
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse'
      description: Successful calculation submission response, returns the job ID
        unique to this calculation and the URL in the Location header to check the
        status of the calculation.
      headers:
        Location:
          description: Relative location to poll for calculation status
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-Units-Limit:
          description: Maximum number of jobs.
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
        X-FactSet-Api-Units-Remaining:
          description: Number of available jobs.
          explode: false
          schema:
            type: string
          style: simple
  schemas:
    ErrorArray:
      description: An array of errors
      properties:
        errors:
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorObject'
          type: array
      type: object
    ErrorCode:
      description: Factset API specific error codes
      enum:
      - notAuthenticated
      - notAuthorized
      - notFound
      - endpointNotFound
      - parameterError
      - genericServerError
      - resourceGone
      - quantityLimitsExceeded
      - universal_screening_parameterError
      - universal_screening_parameterWarning
      type: string
    ErrorObject:
      example:
        id: id
        source:
          parameter: parameter
        title: title
      properties:
        code:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorCode'
        id:
          title: A unique ID for the occurrence of the error. It is advised to log
            this code and include it if you contact FactSet support desk.
          type: string
        source:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/For_errors_and_warnings_found_in_screens__contains_the_paramID_the_error_warning_belongs_to'
        title:
          title: A description of the error
          type: string
      type: object
    PaginationResponse:
      properties:
        isEstimatedTotal:
          title: Denotes if the 'total' property is an estimation
          type: boolean
        next:
          title: Next cursor to be sent, will be null when there are no more results
          type: string
        prev:
          title: Previous cursor, currently not supported
          type: integer
        total:
          title: Total number of rows in the screen
          type: integer
      type: object
    ResourceStatusResponse:
      description: ResourceStatusResponse contains information regarding the status
        of a calculation job
      example:
        data:
          id: id
          error:
            id: id
            source:
              parameter: parameter
            title: title
          status: status
      properties:
        data:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ResourceStatusResponse_data'
      type: object
    ResultsMetadata:
      description: Metadata for results
      properties:
        pagination:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaginationResponse'
      type: object
    ScreenArchiveOFDBParameters:
      example:
        data:
          globalVariablesMap:
            key: globalVariablesMap
          archiveOptions:
            unsplitHistory: true
            timeSeries: true
            archiveType: archiveType
            filename: filename
            overwriteData: true
            archiveDate: archiveDate
            quickColumns: quickColumns
            useReportOrder: true
            autoSymbolUpdates: true
            existed: true
            symbolType: symbolType
          legacyUniverseType: legacyUniverseType
          screenName: screenName
          backtestDate: backtestDate
      properties:
        data:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ScreenArchiveOFDBParameters_data'
      required:
      - data
      type: object
    ScreenCalcParameters:
      example:
        data:
          globalVariablesMap:
            key: globalVariablesMap
          legacyUniverseType: legacyUniverseType
          screenName: screenName
          backtestDate: backtestDate
      properties:
        data:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ScreenCalcParameters_data'
      required:
      - data
      type: object
    inline_response_200_data:
      example:
        id:
        - id
        - id
      properties:
        id:
          items:
            type: string
          type: array
      type: object
    inline_response_200:
      example:
        data:
          id:
          - id
          - id
      properties:
        data:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/inline_response_200_data'
      type: object
    For_errors_and_warnings_found_in_screens__contains_the_paramID_the_error_warning_belongs_to:
      example:
        parameter: parameter
      properties:
        parameter:
          type: string
      title: For errors and warnings found in screens, contains the paramID the error/warning
        belongs to
      type: object
    ResourceStatusResponse_data:
      example:
        id: id
        error:
          id: id
          source:
            parameter: parameter
          title: title
        status: status
      properties:
        error:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorObject'
        id:
          title: ID of the submitted calculation job
          type: string
        status:
          title: Current status of the calculation job
          type: string
      type: object
    ScreenArchiveOFDBParameters_data_archiveOptions:
      example:
        unsplitHistory: true
        timeSeries: true
        archiveType: archiveType
        filename: filename
        overwriteData: true
        archiveDate: archiveDate
        quickColumns: quickColumns
        useReportOrder: true
        autoSymbolUpdates: true
        existed: true
        symbolType: symbolType
      properties:
        archiveDate:
          title: YYYYMMDD date to archive to
          type: string
        archiveType:
          description: Type of archive, i.e. ofdbSymbols, ofdbNts, ofdbQuickNts, ofdb
          type: string
        autoSymbolUpdates:
          title: Flag to enable automatic symbol updates
          type: boolean
        existed:
          title: Indicates that the output file exists
          type: boolean
        filename:
          description: OFDB Filename to archive to
          type: string
        overwriteData:
          title: If true and target file (or date for a time series file) exists,
            it will be cleared before archiving
          type: boolean
        quickColumns:
          title: 'Space delimited list of parameter references to be archived, which
            are UPPERCASED with the #P. omitted'
          type: string
        symbolType:
          title: The symbol type for archiving
          type: string
        timeSeries:
          title: If true, archive 3D time series OFDB
          type: boolean
        unsplitHistory:
          title: Flag indicating split adjust
          type: boolean
        useReportOrder:
          title: If true, archive in report order
          type: boolean
      required:
      - archiveType
      - filename
      type: object
    ScreenArchiveOFDBParameters_data:
      description: Object containing archive request payload
      example:
        globalVariablesMap:
          key: globalVariablesMap
        archiveOptions:
          unsplitHistory: true
          timeSeries: true
          archiveType: archiveType
          filename: filename
          overwriteData: true
          archiveDate: archiveDate
          quickColumns: quickColumns
          useReportOrder: true
          autoSymbolUpdates: true
          existed: true
          symbolType: symbolType
        legacyUniverseType: legacyUniverseType
        screenName: screenName
        backtestDate: backtestDate
      properties:
        archiveOptions:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ScreenArchiveOFDBParameters_data_archiveOptions'
        backtestDate:
          description: Specifies the backtest date used when running the screen, replacing
            the backtest date saved in the screen, can be written in YYYYMMDD, MM/DD/YYYY
